ANTHRA - KYRGYZSTAN (04): (JALAL ABAD) HUMAN
********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: 24 Jun 2015
Source: www.24.kg News Agency [edited]
http://www.eng.24.kg/community/176249-news24.html


At least 6 people were infected with anthrax in Kyrgyzstan in 2015, the press service of the Department of State Sanitary and Epidemiological Supervision of the Ministry of Health Care reported to the 24.kg news agency.

According to the data, 4 cases were registered in January 2015 in Mailu-Suu town, and 2 cases in May in the Suzak district of the Jalal-Abad region.

"Now a man, born in 1975 [apx 40 yrs old], has been taken to hospital with suspected disease. The appropriate medical examination is scheduled," the press service reports.

It is also reported that 2 people in Talas province, 1 in Jalal-Abad, and 2 people in the Osh region were infected with anthrax in 2014.

[Byline: Nurzhamal Ganyeva]

