******
[2]
Date: 24 Jun 2015
Source: AKI Press [edited]
http://www.akipress.com/news:560905


A resident of Changyr village of Suzak district was hospitalized on 22 Jun 2015 with suspected anthrax, the Emergencies Ministry reported.

A 40-year-old resident [sought care at] the infectious department of the regional hospital on 22 Jun 2015. He was subsequently hospitalized with suspected anthrax.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This region of western Kyrgyzstan is under constant threat of anthrax from uncontrolled livestock anthrax in the Furgana valley stretching west in Uzbekistan. See: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/kyrgyzstan_physio-2005.jpg.

The 2 countries need a unified joint control programme to achieve anything in controlling this disease. The human outbreaks follow from slaughtering and butchering animals moribund with anthrax, and consuming and selling the meat in local markets. - Mod MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3461855,138.]
